  "prompt": "If you are a chief financial officer of a start up, is that an employee position?",
  "response": "Yes, the role of Chief Financial Officer (CFO) in a startup is typically an employee position. The CFO is a key executive responsible for managing the financial actions of the company, including financial planning, risk management, record-keeping, and financial reporting. While the specifics can vary depending on the company's structure and stage of development, the CFO is generally considered an integral part of the leadership team and holds a significant amount of responsibility in guiding the company's financial strategy.",
